        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 10:57PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 1057 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lion Hill, or 9 miles east of Yellville, moving southeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Thola...                          Mt Olive in Izard County...
Landis...                         Timbo...
Brandenberg...                    Shipp...
Rea Valley...                     Gunner Pool Campground...
Barkshed Campground...            Calico Rock...
Herron...                         Gorby...
Harriet...                        Cotter...
Gassville...                      Lion Hill...
Push Mountian...                  Rush...
Newnata...                        Buffalo City...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
